  <div class="chart-container"></div>
  <div id="process">
    <h2>The Process</h2>
    <h4>Data Collection</h4>
      <p>Data was obtained from the AngelList API <a href="https://angel.co/api/spec/jobs" target="_blank" class="api">/jobs</a> endpoint, courtesy of whitelist access.<br>
      Only <strong>full-time</strong> jobs in <strong>San Francisco, CA</strong> were analyzed to normalize for differences across job type and geography.<br>
      Each job listing included salary range and <strong>skill tag(s)</strong> that represent skills related to a job.</p>
    <h4>Data Cleanup</h4>
      <p>Jobs with no salary listed or salary of $0 were removed.<br>
      Outliers were also removed, which included a job posting with a salary of $75,000,000</p>
      <p>The below related skill tags were grouped for purposes of analysis.<br>
      If a job posting included two or more of the grouped tags, it was only counted once toward average salary calculation.</p>
      <ul class="grouped-skills">
        <li>Javascript, Javascript Frameworks, Javascript-JS Library</li>
        <li>Python, Django, Django/Flask</li>
        <li>Ruby on Rails, Ruby\Rails, Ruby, Rails, Backend Rails Development</li>
        <li>iOS Development, iOS, Objective C, Objective-C, Swift</li>
        <li>CSS, HTML, HTML5 &amp; CSS3, HTML5  CSS3, HTML/CSS, HTML5/CSS3</li>
        <li>Sales, Sales and Marketing</li>
        <li>Node.js, Nodejs, NodeJs/Express, Node.js Developer, Node JS, Node</li>
        <li>PHP, PHP5, PHP Frameworks, Laravel</li>
      </ul>
    <h4>Data Overview</h4>
      <p><strong>Total Jobs Analyzed:</strong> 2,973<br>
      <strong>Total Skill Tags Analyzed:</strong> 14,885</p>
      <p><strong>Minimum Salary Mean:</strong> $81,737<br>
      <strong>Maximum Salary Mean:</strong> $121,003</p>
      <p><strong>Minimum Salary Range:</strong> $10,000 - 260,000<br>
      <strong>Maximum Salary Range:</strong> $10,000 - 340,000</p>
    <h4>Conclusion</h4>
      <p><strong>JavaScript</strong> is the most in-demand skill with <strong>17.4% (518 of 2,973)</strong> jobs listing JavaScript as a skill tag.<br>
      <strong>Java</strong> is the highest paying skill with 7.8% (233 of 2,973) jobs paying an average of <strong>$121,002</strong>.<br>
      <strong>Sales and Marketing)</strong> is the most in-demand non-technical skill with <strong>12.2% (286 of 2,973)</strong> jobs paying an average of <strong>$84,888</strong>.</p>
