      </div>
      <p>In 2012, Udemy released an <a href="https://blog.udemy.com/modern-language-wars/" target="_blank">infographic</a> comparing modern programming languages. It suggested that <strong>PHP</strong> was the dominant skill, followed by Python and Ruby. This differs from analysis from the AngelList data, which ranked <strong>PHP #45</strong> based on frequency of the skill tag, with only <strong>2.0% (63 of 2,973)</strong> jobs requiring the skill.</p>
      <p>The main reason for this discrepancy is the <strong>source of data</strong> for the Udemy infographic was <a href="http://craigslist.org/" target="_blank">Craigslist</a> and <a href="http://www.monster.com/" target="_blank">Monster</a>, websites for general job listings. Data for this data visualization project was from <a href="http://angel.co/" target="_blank">AngelList</a>, a website for startups. Additionally, Udemy did not include JavaScipt in their research.</p>
